Energy Capital Partners Hires Banks to Explore Sale, IPO of EquiPower
Barclays and Goldman Sachs Working With EquiPower

 






By

Gillian Tan


Gillian Tan
The Wall Street Journal
BiographyGillian Tan




  May 28, 2014 6:33 p.m. ET





Private-equity firm Energy Capital Partners has hired banks to explore a sale or initial public offering of power-generation company EquiPower Resources Corp., according to people familiar with the matter.  Barclays PLC and Goldman Sachs Group Inc. are working with EquiPower, which owns and operates a collection of power plants in Connecticut, Illinois, Massachusetts, Ohio and Pennsylvania, according to the people. The company,...
  


